ENTRY            A0187   20260126   20260317   20260317       A129
SUBENT        A0187001   20260126   20260317   20260317       A129
BIB                 17         48
TITLE      Excitation functions for the production of 76Kr
           and 77Kr
AUTHOR     (D.De Jong,G.A.Brinkman,L.Lindner)
REFERENCE  (J,ARI,30,188,1979)
INSTITUTE  (2NEDIKO)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2NEDKVI)
           (CYCLO,2BLGLVN)
SAMPLE     The irradiations were performed on stacks of pressed
           pellets of anhydrous 'K-Br', diam. = 1.3cm, thickness
           150-250 mg/cm2) of natural isotopic composition. At
           regular interval aluminum (0.1 mm thick, diam. 1.3 cm)
            and copper foils (0.1 mm thick, diam.1.3cm) were
           inserted between 'K-Br' pellets as proton current
           monitor.
METHOD     (STTA,EXTB,ACTIV)
           (GSPEC)
DETECTOR   (GELI)
MONITOR    (13-AL-27(P,X)11-NA-24,CUM,SIG)
           (29-CU-63(P,X)29-CU-61,CUM,SIG)
           (29-CU-63(P,2N)30-ZN-62,,SIG)
MONIT-REF  (,I.Tobailem+,R,CEA-N-1466,(1),1971) For Al-27
           (B0054005,J.W.Meadows,J,PR,91,885,1953)
           (B0054003,J.W.Meadows,J,PR,91,885,1953)
           Additional reference see in original paper.
DECAY-MON  (11-NA-24,15.HR,DG,1368.,1.)
           (29-CU-61,3.41HR,DG,283.,0.13)
           (30-ZN-62,9.3HR,DG,548.,0.141)
ADD-RES    (TTY-C) For Kr-76 and Kr-77 activity produced during
           1 hour irradiation.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR,10.,15.) Error is estimated as 10-15%
           mainly due to the error in the excitation functions of
           the monitor reactions used.
ANALYSIS   (CORAB)
COMMENT    /by Compiler/ Compiler believes that correction on
           isotopic composition was included by authors.
STATUS     (APRVD) By G.A.Brinkman.
HISTORY    (19830404C)
           (19850305A) See Brinkman's remarks.
           (19991020A) Some reaction lines are corrected. Lower
            case
           (20011010A) Date is corrected
           (20020321U) Last checking has been done.
           (20160318U) SD: MONIT-REF corrected, SF9=EXP deleted
           from REACTION code; EN-ERR -> EN-ERR-DIG in Subent 001.
           BIB update. RAD-DET deleted from Subents (information
           presented in DECAY-DATA). ANALYSIS (AREA) deleted (not
           relevant).
           (20260126A) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              48
COMMON               1          3
EN-ERR-DIG
MEV
        0.3
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           55
SUBENT        A0187002   20260126   20260317   20260317       A129
BIB                  5          5
